	<principle>
	<title>The Work-Energy Theorem</title>
	<statement>
	  <p>The net work done by external forces on an object or system is equal to the change in total energy of that system: <m>W_{net,external} = \Delta E</m>. </p>
	</statement>
	</principle>

	<exercises>

			<exercise>
			  <p>How do you think you would calculate the net work if more than one force were acting on an object or system? </p>
			</exercise>
			
			<exercise>
			  <p>What are some different kinds of energy you could imagine changing? </p>
			</exercise>
		
		</exercises>
	
